    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-07T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-07T20:00:00-05:00" n="134"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/729: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The First Vice President of Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Larco</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName> [<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1941-12-07T22:00:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1941-12-07T20:00:00-05:00">undated</date>].<lb/>[Received
                        December 7, 1941—10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Beg you to accept assurance sincere sympathy, adherence and wishes for triumph of
                    democracy, requesting you to transmit (same) to His Excellency the President.
                    Cordially.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Larco</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
